    "what_description": "Sphenomeris angustifolia is a species of fern within the family Lindsaeaceae. It is a terrestrial fern with a rhizome that produces fronds that are linear, lanceolate, and pinnate, with segments that are 5-10 cm long and 2-3 cm wide. The plant has an indusium that is membranous and has a cuneate base, with a sori that is continuous and anadromous. Sphenomeris angustifolia is a diploid plant with 2n = 40 chromosomes and its leaves are dimorphic, with sterile and fertile fronds differing in size and morphology. The species is found in tropical and subtropical regions, particularly in Southeast Asia and the Pacific Islands.",
