    "benefits": "Sphenomeris angustifolia, also known as the Tibetan mountain cabbage or Tibetan mustard cabbage, is a plant with potential health benefits. It is traditionally used in Tibetan medicine to treat various ailments, including digestive issues and respiratory problems. The plant is believed to have anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties, which may help protect against cell damage and reduce inflammation. Additionally, Sphenomeris angustifolia may have antimicrobial properties, which could aid in the prevention of infections. Further research is needed to confirm the specific health benefits of this plant.",
