    "intro": "Sphenomeris angustifolia, also known as Chinese Angelica or Narrow-leaved Sphenomeris, is a plant species belonging to the family Araliaceae. It has been traditionally used in Chinese medicine to treat various health issues, including fever, rheumatism, and digestive problems, due to its anti-inflammatory, antibacterial, and antiviral properties. The bioactive constituents of Sphenomeris angustifolia include coumarins, lignans, and sesquiterpenes, which contribute to its medicinal effects. In traditional Chinese medicine, the plant is often prepared as a decoction, tincture, or dried root, which is used to treat a range of health conditions, including colds, coughs, and respiratory infections."
